query: As of August 2023, who is the only winner of the US version of Survivor to be born in the month of May?

answer_raw.final_answer: There are no winners born in May.

facts.fact: Bob Crowley, winner of Survivor: Gabon, was born on February 25, 1951.
James Thomas Jr., winner of Survivor: Tocantins, was born on June 23, 1984.
Natalie White, winner of Survivor: Samoa, was born on April 22, 1983.
Richard Hatch, the first winner of Survivor (Borneo), was born on April 8, 1961.
Sandra Diaz-Twine is a two-time winner of Survivor, winning Pearl Islands and Heroes vs. Villains.
